title: Storing your dotfiles in git so they can be checked out elsewhere
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

When you want your `.*rc` files (`.bashrc`, `.vimrc`, `.bash_login`) to be cloned into a new machine, you can [[just use symlinks|https://unix.stackexchange.com/a/586665/3570]] to make it happen.

That way you don't have to mix the rest of your home directory into your git repo where you store the files.